<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="772" type="discussion">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hulva &amp; Benda" authorityYear="2004" box="[2058,2296,2867,2900]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="772" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hanaki">Pipistrellus hanaki</taxonomicName>
1s considered closely related to P. pipustrellus and 
<taxonomicName box="[2427,2584,2907,2940]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Pipustrellus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="14" pageNumber="772" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pygmaeus">P. pygmaeus</taxonomicName>
, but it differs from them based on a number of morphological characteristics. Pipustrellushanaki, P. creticus, and 
<taxonomicName box="[2398,2551,3033,3058]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Pipustrellus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="14" pageNumber="772" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pygmaeus">P. pygmaeus</taxonomicName>
form a monophyletic clade thatis sister to 
<taxonomicName box="[1931,2096,3064,3097]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Pipustrellus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="14" pageNumber="772" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pipistrellus">P. pipistrellus</taxonomicName>
. It previously included P. creticus as a distinct subspecies, but genetic data support its recognition as a distinct species. Monotypic.
</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
